programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Estelle Bell

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Scrubs No More

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Changing For The Better

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Crystal Clear

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: It's a year since we left Leopard's Den and much has changed. The animal hospital has been rebuilt and is now up and running. It's a big day for all the family as Danny has been fighting for custody of Evan and today they will learn the judge's decision.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny and Evan's life on the run doesn't start well when Danny falls asleep at the wheel and drives into a ditch. They have to enlist a local farmer, Johann, to winch them out.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny is asked by the State Vet to help control an outbreak of rabies in the National Park. When Vanessa is concerned for the animals at Mara, Danny assures her it's a long way away and advises her to continue with business as usual.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: It's the day before Rosie's wedding. Danny is proud of his daughter and determined to feed her up now that she's eating for two. All the family are excited about the imminent return of Caroline, especially Du Plessis who can't wait to see his fiancé.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Alice and Danny are called out by a farmer who's trapped an African Wild Dog. As they're even more endangered than cheetahs and much more vicious, Danny and Alice are amazed to see one up close.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: When Du Plessis instructs the family to be around for dinner, they are intrigued to hear he's planning a big announcement. However, he won't be drawn on details and tells them to be patient.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Alice and Danny are delighted when the Animal Hospital is given responsibility for the rescue and conservation of animals in the region – it's a big achievement after all their hard work.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny and Alice are concerned about a missing male giraffe but Du Plessis is confident he can find him. He's as good as his word but they're upset to discover Mara lions have killed the giraffe.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: The chopper crewmen have their hands full with five badly injured patients after a car crash near Waiuku, and a massive motorcycle pile-up leaves injured bikers all over the road, and a man may have broken his neck after falling from his horse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: As a weather bomb hits, the chopper crew set out on one of the most challenging missions they have ever undertaken 20 miles off shore, a man lays face down at Muriwai beach unable to move.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: A hang glider pilot may have broken his back after a heavy crash-landing, a Manaia man is in a bad way after coming off a sea biscuit at high speed, and a crashed Waikato driver needs an urgent air-lift to hospital to save his life.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: It is the most extraordinary case diplomat Tom Walter has ever seen - 18 and 16 year-old Aussie brothers, Aiden and Jackson have been abandoned by their parents and left to fend for themselves.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's judgement day for abandoned Aussie brothers, Aiden and Jackson. After hours of questioning, Indonesian Immigration officials have confiscated the boy's passports and put them under strict house arrest.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: 59-year-old Joanne came to Thailand for a body makeover. She's had a tummy tuck and liposuction to look her best for her daughter's wedding. She loses her passport and the wound from her tummy tuck gets infected, Joanne finds herself stuck in Thailand.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: Wayne has no money, no passport and a mountain of debt. Homeless and out of options, he's back at the Consulate in Bali with sobering news. But can consular officer, Tom Walter trust his story?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6
programme.desc: 56-year-old Michael is living every parent's worst nightmare. His six-year-old son Dylan has been missing for three months now. His ex-wife didn't return him after a routine weekend visit and now he fears that she's trying to smuggle him out of Bali.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 1

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 3

programme.title: Paranormal State: Return of the Dead: Glove II

programme.desc: Ryan brings PRS to his hometown of Sumter, SC to investigate a chilling case where a young boy was tragically shot and killed on a front doorstep while trick-or-treating on Halloween.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Mothman
programme.desc: Ryan takes his team to Point Pleasant, West Virginia to investigate his own personal holy grail of paranormal lore: the mysterious Mothman.

programme.title: Paranormal State: First Contact
programme.desc: Washington State, a hotbed of unexplained paranormal activity. Between possible UFOs in the sky and winged creatures in the woods, Ryan and his team are forced to face their fears and deal with the question: Are we truly alone in the universe?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Vendetta
programme.desc: P.R.S. investigates claims of supernatural revenge in the Pennsylvania Poconos. When a client's new boyfriend moves in, does the paranormal move in with him? Or did her ex put a hex on her house and the entire family?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dwelling of the Dead
programme.desc: A single mom claims she is being physically assaulted by a spirit in her Kentucky home. Ryan first explores a natural explanation for the alleged phenomena. But the client's five-year-old son also sees spirits, and his sightings appear to line up.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Ladder

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Devil in Syracuse
programme.desc: The clients are new, but the spirit is all too familiar as Ryan Buell prepares himself to battle the taunting demon that has been following him.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dead Legends
programme.desc: PRS and Psychic/Medium Chip Coffey investigate the famed Hotel Conneaut in northern Pennsylvania. Heavy doors opening on their own, sightings of a boy, a bride and a menacing butcher have the hotel's staff on edge.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Shadow Caster
programme.desc: PRS investigates an Alabama home where clients, Georgiana and her two daughters, are so terrified, they moved out after only 18 months. They have seen shadow figures, been touched and have a recorded EVP stating, "Look at me, get out of here."

programme.title: Paranormal State: Satan's Soldier

programme.title: Most Haunted: Muckleburgh

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tamworth Castle

programme.title: Most Haunted: Owlpen Manor

programme.title: Most Haunted: Craig-Y-Nos
programme.desc: This derelict castle in the heart of Wales has been home to a famous opera singer and a World War II hospital. This beautiful building is so haunted that the team has to spend the night.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Jamaica Inn

programme.title: Most Haunted: Croxteth Hall
programme.desc: A manor in Liverpool awaits the team in a place that time forgot. A boy standing beside the fireplace in the dining room and a horrifying hooded man are among several ghosts reported here.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Hellfire Caves
programme.desc: The team encounters ghostly lights and voices in the Hellfire Caves. These legendary tunnels were once home to the notorious Hellfire Club, practitioners of satanic rituals, murder and debauchery.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Manor House
programme.desc: The team investigate the Manor House in Ferryhill, County Durham. Now a hotel, this historic house has had many uses over the centuries and is said to house several ghosts.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Crystal Clear

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Teacher Learns A Lesson

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Serving Up a New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting Back to Hog Heaven

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Shopping For a New Look
programme.desc: Karyn is a busy working wife and mother of three, whose current frumpy appearance isn't matching the way she feels inside. It's the goal of our experts to fashion Karyn a more youthful, trendsetting look as we try make her look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Richard Power "One Year On"
programme.desc: Last year, 35 year old Richard Power was living life to the limits – and it showed. A year later, we recap Richard's rocky relationship with our femme fatale of flair – and see whether a catch-up with Nicky will set things straight.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Bringing Out The Spunk
programme.desc: Cat has a dream job working with rock stars and she lost 125 pounds with diet and exercise. She's worked hard to get where she is, but its left her looking more 30-something than 20-something. Our team is ready to jam on her makeover and do what it takes.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rapunzel, Rapunzel, We Must Cut Your Hair!

programme.sub-title: Rapunzel, Rapunzel, We Must Cut Your Hair!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Make Under

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Sky Hag To Sky Hottie

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: High Flying Look
programme.desc: Joanne's been soaring the blue skies for the past 20 years as a pilot. Flying at high altitudes in the bright sun all these years has left her skin damaged and wrinkled. Watch our experts bring out her feminine side and drop the years from her appearance.

programme.sub-title: Saying "I Do" To A New Look

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: River of Blood
programme.desc: Two hunters discover a blood-drenched car, its owner riddled with buckshot. Lt. Joe Kenda learns the car was reported stolen the day before, he follows its trail to a group of unlikely suspects.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Gut Instinct
programme.desc: When a soon-to-be grandmother doesn’t come home from work and the investigation unfolds, Lt. Joe Kenda realizes they could be dealing with a fledgling serial killer.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Blood Sisters
programme.desc: The bullet-ridden bodies of two sisters are found in a suburban house that’s littered with mysterious clues. Joe Kenda learns that the two unassuming young mothers shared an explosive secret.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Preying on the Innocent
programme.desc: When the son of a prominent politician is murdered in his basement, Lt. Joe Kenda feels pressure from City Hall to solve the case.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Bring My Baby Home
programme.desc: A four-week-old girl is kidnapped, leaving her mother in anguish and police scrambling to find her. Joe Kenda and Robert Sapp fear she’s been sold on the black market… or worse.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Manifesto
programme.desc: A cabin on the slopes of Pikes Peak catches fire, and a young sheriff’s deputy is posted to guard the scene overnight--then he’s found dead in his patrol car the next morning.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Joker In the Pack
programme.desc: A card game is interrupted by gunfire, leaving a young man dead. Lt. Joe Kenda soon learns the seeds of his destruction were sewn earlier the same day.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Bad Moon Rising
programme.desc: Night before Halloween, a real-life nightmare unfolds when a young man is found clinging to life. The case takes a dark turn when Lt. Joe Kenda learns there is a second victim somewhere in the woods.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Hounded By Fear
programme.desc: Melody is terrified of dogs, while pool man Tom will even leave a job site if one is near. Cesar helps them deal with their fears and anxieties.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Anger Management
programme.desc: Cesar helps the lead singer of Rooney with his aggressive pit bull, while writer and producer Paul needs help with his two Boston terriers.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: ATF Dog
programme.desc: Gavin, a decorated K-9 explosive sniffing agent for the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms, and Explosives, is terrified of loud noises. Cesar uses some creative tactics to rehabilitate him.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Peanut & Chico, Leroy Brown, and Tucker
programme.desc: Fighting Chihuahuas learn to get along. A dog with extreme attachment issues learns to relax. A couple’s border collie Tucker is obsessed with moving water, to a point that’s become dangerous.
programme.sub-title: Peanut & Chico, Leroy Brown, and Tucker

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Seven, Sara, and Madeliene
programme.desc: Jillian Michael’s Greyhound mix barks and nips at her horse. A German Shorthaired Pointer is an escape artist. A Yorkie demonstrates fear aggression of brooms and car windshield wipers.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Widow’s Dilemma
programme.desc: After Noelle’s husband unexpectedly passed away, their two dogs developed behavioral issues. The Wilson family’s Italian Greyhound Hula, snaps and growls at certain family members.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Made in Japan, Lawnmower Licker
programme.desc: Marley, a neglected Shiba Inu from Japan, develops aggression towards dogs and people. Piper, a Wire Fox Terrier obsessively tries to get to and lick the lawnmower engine.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Kobe, Banjo, and Kisses
programme.desc: An aggressive one-eyed Australian shepherd needs special treatment. A traumatized black and tan coonhound is terrified of people, a Maltese gets a little too excited when guests drop by.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Being Pamela Anderson
programme.desc: Carolyn Anderson, a 29 year-old women from the UK, is addicted to transforming herself into Baywatch beauty Pamela Anderson.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Air Freshener / Long Neck
programme.desc: In this episode we meet Evelyn, who drinks air freshener every day, and Sydney, who is obsessed with having the world's longest neck.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Older Women/ Madonna
programme.desc: 31-year-old Kyle is addicted to dating much older women, over the age of 65. Adam is intent upon becoming Madonna.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 3
programme.desc: In this special episode of My Strange Addiction, we count down the ten most shocking addictions ever featured on the series and provide updates.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Drywall/Shower Drain Hair Collector
programme.desc: Evan has spent the last six years sneaking into bathrooms because he is addicted to collecting shower drain hair. And Nicole, has spent the last seven years secretly eating drywall.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Extreme Cycling/Taxidermy
programme.desc: Tom is so addicted to cycling that he spends at least six hours a day riding. Divya loves spending her time searching for dead animals on the side of the road and stuffing them.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Rocks/Pillow Obsessed
programme.desc: Theresa has been eating rocks for more than 20 years and can't stop. Meanwhile, Tamara carries around her childhood pillow Boo everywhere she goes.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Bathes in Bleach/Eats Plastic
programme.desc: Kailyn has eaten plastic every day for more than eleven years, consuming more than 150 pounds. Meanwhile, Gloria, 28, has taken her addiction to bleach to the extreme by bathing in it daily.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Carrying My Husband’s Urn
programme.desc: Casie has been so shocked by the sudden death of her husband, Shawn, that she takes his urn everywhere she goes. But she has now started eating his ashes.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Cat Food/Smells Moth Balls
programme.desc: Mary has taken her addiction to cat food to the extreme, consuming 900 cat treats and several cans of food every day. Meanwhile, Alicia has been addicted to smelling mothballs for 15 years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Sniffs Pine Cleaner/Road Kill Addict
programme.desc: Jillian is addicted to smelling pine cleaner and can't go more than 15 minutes without a fix, using up to six bottles a week. Scott is obsessed with picking up dead animals from the road.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Identical Twin Obsession / Eats Mattresses
programme.desc: Twins Amy and Becky are addicted to being identical, looking alike, acting alike, and even weighing their meals to stay the same size. Jennifer is addicted to eating mattresses.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to a Doll/Eats Plastic Bags
programme.desc: Robert, a 23-year-old man who's addicted to eating plastic newspaper bags, an addition so intense, that he goes days without food. Catherine, a 48-year-old woman whose best friend is a doll.
programme.sub-title: Addicted to a Doll/Eats Plastic Bags

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Dangerous Trails
programme.desc: Brandon and Hanna want a home on an isolated lake far into the Alaskan wild, where there’s no way in but off-roading through trails of mud or landing on water.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: No Roads In
programme.desc: Dave and Wendy want a remote cabin where they can escape to the Alaskan frontier way of life, places so hidden that the only way there is by off-road vehicle and no outhouse is safe from hungry bears.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Jaws, Claws & Beaver Fever
programme.desc: Shane and Erica want a home in the Alaskan wild, where it’s so remote, the only way in is by a monster 8-wheeler. Homeowners beware! Bears attack the properties and beavers infect the drinking water.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Hot Tubs and Gators
programme.desc: Duck, Lathan, & Flip are tired of traveling each weekend to their favorite place to enjoy bayou living. They’re willing to do anything to buy a home if they can hunt gators right out their back door.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Lakes for the Champ
programme.desc: “Catfish” Jack Clampit and his daughter, Amanda, love hand-grabbing catfish, so he and Amanda are searching for a camp that will accommodate both their families…and their appetite for catfish.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Starter Homes
programme.desc: Josh McIntire is an avid duck hunter and fisherman and he hopes to find a house where he can do just that. He’s bringing his life-long best friend, Hanna, for guidance.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Rolling on the River
programme.desc: Bryan Fassbender and Stephanie Robichaux are self described work-a-holics who just want to have a weekend houseboat on the Pearl River, and are willing to live off the grid.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Boaters Beware
programme.desc: Matt and Laurie aren’t your ordinary couple looking for a turnkey home. They love fixing places up. They look at three unusual homes on Louisiana oxbows.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Storm Deals
programme.desc: David and Jackie love bayou life in Mississippi. With their two sons away at college, they’re looking to downsize on the water. They’re looking for a fixer upper they can make their own.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Hurricane Homes
programme.desc: Jeff and Amelia Harding cruise the Mississippi Gulf Coast in search of a new house. Amelia lost her home in Katrina, so they’re scouring the coast for a house that can stand up to a hurricane.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Beaches vs. Bayous
programme.desc: CJ, who grew up on a shrimp boat in Louisiana, and Marty, from Los Angeles, are looking for a weekend getaway but can’t agree whether it will be on the bayou or the beach.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Airboat Homes
programme.desc: They’re big, loud, fast and can traverse anything. Airboats aren’t just a novelty in Louisiana, they’re essential—join the Fradellas as they search for an airboat accessible home.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Louisiana Luxury
programme.desc: Larry and Amber Douglas started a business that has become a million-dollar operation. They’re looking to upgrade their lifestyle, but still want a place with a down home bayou feel.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cruisin For A Bruisin
programme.desc: Join Jill and Marvin as they comb Belle River for the perfect floating home—something that’ll get them back in the swamps and back to their bayou roots.
